Author: lukechilds#2707
Content: You can  get access directly to mm methods from the JS console

Author: lukechilds#2707
Content: it's a bit easier than using the CLI

Author: lukechilds#2707
Content: and it'll automatically use the correct port/userpass

Author: lukechilds#2707
Content:
Open the devtools and run:

```
_api.debug({method: 'swapstatus', requestid: 174600499, quoteid: 4137389265})
```

in the console

Author: lukechilds#2707
Content: obviously change the params to whatever you want

Author: lukechilds#2707
Content: give it a few seconds and it will dump the response in the console

Author: lukechilds#2707
Content: You can do any mm command this way

Author: lukechilds#2707
Content: @Cryptoon I wouldn't recommend flipping the pair, choose the pair you want to use and then place buys and sells

Author: lukechilds#2707
Content: a BTC/KMD sell is the same as a KMD/BTC buy

Author: lukechilds#2707
Content: but if you want to flip them, you only need to change one currency on the drop down, if it's the same as the other side it'll flip

Author: lukechilds#2707
Content:
e.g if you're on KMD/BTC:
- Change the base currency from KMD to BTC
- The quote currency (BTC) will automatically swap to KMD
